<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,258,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,258,284]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Comments:</emphasis>
Three individuals within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1907" box="[645,844,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Neoconocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[645,844,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Neoconocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were classified as follows. Individuals, all males, present (1) a black spot at the base of each tibia, (2) narrow wings, of a single colour, twice as long as femur III, (3) rounded fastigium, longer than wide, with whitish apex, (4) apex of vertex green, the same way as the rest of the body, and (5) mirror straight at its anterior margin, concave at the medial/posterior margin and slightly curved at the lateral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,258,465]" box="[199,589,438,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,438,464]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
: Sound not recorded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
